{"tipType":"windowShade","windowShade":{"windowShadeType":"framing","layout":"mediaLeft","initialOpenState":true,"content":"###Water Cycle Review (Optional)

The water cycle (also known as the hydrologic cycle) is a foundational concept for understanding the dynamics of watersheds. If your students would benefit from a review of the water cycle before this lesson or before beginning the WATERS Curriculum, we suggest using the USGS Water Cycle for Schools Interactive <a href="https://water.usgs.gov/edu/watercycle-kids-int.html" target="_blank">(https://water.usgs.gov/edu/watercycle-kids-int.html)</a>. This online, interactive diagram of the water cycle in English includes pop-up balloons that describe the terms included in the USGS diagram. There are three versions of the water cycle diagram with different numbers of terms explained (Beginner - 6 terms, Intermediate - 16 terms, and Advanced - 33 terms). 

Unfortunately, this interactive is not available in Spanish at this time. There is a non-interactive Spanish language version of the same diagram available on the USGS website that could be printed out or viewed when ELL students are using the online Water Cycle for Schools Interactive <a href="https://www.usgs.gov/media/images/el-ciclo-del-agua-para-ni-os-water-cycle-schools-spanish" target="_blank">(https://www.usgs.gov/media/images/el-ciclo-del-agua-para-ni-os-water-cycle-schools-spanish)</a>. More information on Spanish language resources from USGS can be found on the USGS website (https://www.usgs.gov/special-topic/water-science-school/science/el-ciclo-del-agua-water-cycle-schools-spanish).","content2":"","mediaType":"none","mediaCaption":"Last, First. "Title of Work." Year created. Site Title [OR] Publisher. Gallery [OR] Location. http://www.url.com.","mediaURL":""}}

